HEADWORD: Brazil nut
<hw>Bra*zil" nut`</hw> <pr>(br⟦adot⟧*z⟦icr⟧l" n⟦ucr⟧t`)</pr>.
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An oily, three-sided nut, the seed of the
<spn>Bertholletia excelsa</spn>; the cream nut.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ From eighteen to twenty-four of the seeds or
⟦ldquo⟧nuts⟦rdquo⟧ grow in a hard and nearly globular shell.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

